parameters.content:
## Structured Output 

**Generate Outlines** node is using structured output defined in system prompt in node **LLM Params**. Payload for API call defined in node **Define Schema** where target object schema is defined, see left ->
```json
{
  "articleOutlines": [
    {
      "title": "",
      "markdownOutline": ""
    }
  ]
}
```

## Object Schema for Structured Output 

Using the following schema in **Define Schema** node to define **Generate Outlines** structured output. LLM will return list of sample outlines with `title` and `markdownOutline` properties
```json
{
  "schema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "articleOutlines": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "title": { "type": "string" },
                "markdownOutline": { "type": "string" }
              },
              "required": [ "title", "markdownOutline" ],
              "additionalProperties": false
            }
          }
        },
        "required": [ "articleOutlines" ],
        "additionalProperties": false
      }
}
```

parameters.jsonBody:
={
  "model": "{{ $('LLM Params').item.json.simple_model }}",
  "tools": [
    { "type": "web_search_preview" }
  ],
  "input": "Locate **exactly three** authoritative articles published **within the last 12 months** on “{{ $json.output }}”. Prefer peer-reviewed journals, major newspapers, or official (.gov, .edu, well-established .org) sources.  Prefer articles in {{ $('Language').item.json.main_language }}  

Return an **ordered Markdown list** (1., 2., 3.), where each item contains:  
• **Title** – the full headline  
• **Source & Date** – outlet name, DD MMM YYYY  
• **URL** – canonical link  
• **Outline** – 4-6 concise bullet points summarising the article’s main structure or argument flow.  

Keep each outline under 120 words and avoid duplicate sources."
}

